ontainer\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"caption\"><p>Management courses are one of the most popular choices\u00a0of graduation subject for any student in India after class 12th. They offer plenty of employment as well as higher education opportunities for a student. Here are some reasons why you should consider taking up a management course after class 12th.<\/p><\/div><div class=\"newAlertButton\">\u00a0<\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-e92b79a elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"e92b79a\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-181c4758\" data-id=\"181c4758\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e879765 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"e879765\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"792\" height=\"315\" src=\"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/pcs-white-logo.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c3d1b2d elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c3d1b2d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h4 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">bachelors in managment<\/h4>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-12af36d elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"12af36d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5db2697 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"5db2697\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Class 12th or Intermediate is a very important milestone in any student&#8217;s life. It is also a very crucial time as the choices made by a student at this stage may define what they do in their long-term career. A student may also feel pressurised to take up a course or stream just because their parents think it is best or just because their friends are going for it.<\/p><p>A part of this is because there are innumerable options of streams, degrees, courses and colleges a student can take up after class 12th, and with nobody there to explain the pros and cons and scope of these options, life can get confusing very quickly. At this point, it is very important for a student to keep a steady head and weigh all options carefully before investing their time, money and efforts into pursuing a course.<\/p><p>One of the most popular streams of higher education in India is management. Management courses offer a number of benefits to a student and there are a number of reasons why management courses should be considered by a student after class 12th.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-d1f4381 elementor-section-boxed element